CAPE TOWN - There are demands for more action to curb gang-related violence on the Cape Flats. Western Cape Community Safety Committee Chairperson, Reagan Allen, said the deployment of the SANDF alone was never going to solve the problem. READ: Far from Cape Town tourist sites, a gangland battle rages A police officer was gunned down by four men in his home last week. It's believed the killing is gang-related. READ: Soldiers deployed to Cape Town accused of assault "The SANDF was not going to be a silver bullet," said Allen. He stated the need for improved crime intelligence and an improvement in the societal approach to gun violence and gangsterism.